data.text:
Stacey Dash is secretly married to Jeffrey Marty.

The 51-year-old actress - who shot to fame playing Dionne Davenport in 1995 flick 'Clueless' - reportedly tied the knot with lawyer Jeffrey shortly after she withdrew from her campaign for Congress in California in April 2018, according to the New York Post newspaper's Page Six column.

It has been claimed that the couple married just 10 days after meeting.

Stacey's manager Kerry Jones confirmed to the publication that the pair are husband and wife but shared no details of when they met or why the nuptials were conducted in secret.

Kerry said: "They wanted it on the D.L. [down low]."

Stacey - who is Damon Dash's cousin - had filed in February to run in California's 44th congressional district announcing that her goal was to "free people from the shackles of a plantation mentality" but she dropped out just one month later blaming "the overall bitterness surrounding our political process".

The 'Wild About Harry' star has been married three times before, to Brian Lovell, James Maby and Emmanuel Xuereb, and two children; 26-year-old son Austin Williams from her relationship with singer Christopher Williams and 15-year-old daughter Lola Lovell from her union to producer Brian.
